      • ttl

        public abstract int ttl()
        A 32-bit integer (range from 0 to 4294967295) that represents the duration in seconds that the record is cached. Zero indicates that the record should not be cached. The default value is undefined which indicates that the record inherits the TTL value of the zone. Specify a TTL value to override the TTL value at the zone level.

        TTL (Time-To-Live) How often a copy of the record stored in cache (local storage) must be updated (fetched from original storage) or discarded. Shorter TTLs mean records are fetched more often (access is slower, data is more current). Longer TTLs mean records are fetched from less often (access is faster, data is less current). The default value is 5 sec. Note: When you make changes to a resource record, It could take up to the length of the TTL time for the change to propagate.

      • tlsVerify

        public abstract boolean tlsVerify()
        Checks if TLS certificate validation is enabled for communicating with Infoblox.

      • trustStore

        public abstract Optional<String> trustStore()
        PKCS#12 (.p12) file path contains trusted CA certs. If the path starts with classpath:, it will be loaded from classpath. This is optional and required only if tlsVerify() is enabled.

      • trustStorePassword

        public abstract Optional<String> trustStorePassword()
        TrustStore password. Default password is 'changeit'. This is optional and required only if tlsVerify() is enabled.

      • timeout

        public abstract int timeout()
        IBA WAPI connection/read/write timeout. Default is 10 sec

      • debug

        public abstract boolean debug()
        Enable http curl logging for debugging.

      • createMXRec

        public MX createMXRec(String domainName,
                      String mailExchanger,
                      int preference)
               throws IOException
        Creates mail exchange (MX) record for a domain name.
        Parameters:
        domainName - domain name.
        mailExchanger - Mail server host responsible for accepting email messages on behalf of the domain name. The host name must map directly to one or more address record (A, or AAAA) in the DNS, and must not point to any CNAME records.
        preference - A value used to prioritize mail delivery if multiple mail servers are available, smaller distances are more preferable.
        Returns:
        MX record.
